    "faqs": [
      {
        "question": " Is the 3D CT PNS scan painful?",
        "answer": " No. It’s a non-invasive, painless procedure that takes just a few minutes.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "How much radiation is involved?",
        "answer": " Approximately 0.3–0.6 mSv—lower than a standard chest CT and considered safe.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I eat before the scan?",
        "answer": "\n Yes for plain CT PNS; 4-hour fasting is needed only if contrast is used.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": " Will my insurance cover the cost?",
        "answer": " Most policies cover CT PNS under ENT diagnostic benefits; Cadabams Diagnostics has cashless tie-ups.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": " Can children undergo CT PNS?",
        "answer": " Yes, from age 5 onwards with paediatric low-dose protocols.\n"
      }
